The correct form is There are many options to choose healthier food instead of junk food., not There is.  Heres why    Grammar rule  There is  used with singular nouns  e.g. There is one option.  There are  used with plural nouns  e.g. There are many options.  Since options is plural, you must use are.
Why use are instead of is?

Excellent question!   We use are instead of is because of agreement between the verb and the noun  this is called subjectverb agreement.  Lets break it down    1. The structure There is / There are  In English, the verb (is / are) must match the real subject that comes after it.  There is + singular noun  There is one option.  There are + plural noun  There are many options.   2. In your sentence  There are many options to choose healthier food instead of junk food.  The word options is plural, so the verb must also be plural  are.  If it were only one option, you would say:  There is one option to choose healthier food.
What is subject-verb agreement?

Subjectverb agreement means that the verb in a sentence must match the subject in number (singular or plural). In other words:  A singular subject needs a singular verb  A plural subject needs a plural verb
